posts.body:
It truly is quite the new adventure. A bunch of internet nobodies against the world - building a new place to shitpost.
Just sorted 08chan's downloaded data by music. I enjoy all the classical music anons have shared, "Prelude: Song of the Gulls" is my 08chan Theme now. This is our new home.

The ZeroNet homepage says that 2300 files still need updating for the past 96 hours of non stop seeding. Any chance it will go down or is it there forever to trigger my ocd?

>>b3d7d1e9-0627-4ce6-86c8-7eb1979b0742
Now it's all looking awesome.
Files to update are up to 39000 over night, already 12gb of data and finally a steady seeding upload. Board looks sexy and the post count went through the roof.
I'm all set, the censorship apocalypse can come any time now.

The current number seems to be around 6600 peers. These are people or computers, that have opened up 08chan at least once and are currently online / have zeronet turned on.

During the golden days of 4chan we hated the underage b&, then we hated the reddit posters and now we hate on a new kind of newfag. The world hates us, let's not hate ourselves. You were a mere newfag yourself once. Now look at you, all strong and on the heels of heretics. Believe.

Everything else is beyond retarded. Blocking for Gore and "sick fuck drawings" is both unrealistic and missing the point of board culture. There is no way people will keep up reporting that.
Fuck off with that idea, people aren't coming here for the family friendly content.

>>142d5f87-51af-43c5-9051-5557af73e683

08chan is not exactly user friendly, it confused me as well in the beginning, how some posts would not go through even though I had ZeroID going.
Finding that 0Menu alone was quite a hurdle. Who the fuck does click and drag on a desktop.

posts.subject: Search engine thread
posts.body:
>Just learned, that DuckDuckGo is more of a meta search engine itself. Pulling data from Yahoo, which in turn pulls from bing, unless you are searching in russian, at which point it pulls from Yandex.
>In essence, it's using bing anyways, unless I'm misunderstanding something.
Any good alternatives?

>>e6c515ca-e19b-4ec2-b912-c6049d5107b4
My comfy level is already through the roof :3

>>7cfba737-8bb7-4c9a-9761-73454b198d63
Nah, have some faith. It's quite comfy here and I have high hopes for 8kun.

>>f5b817c7-55b6-4a25-a6e5-aa80c05d1e23
I just double checked tracert from two different connections. I see nothing of the sort.
Nothing going through any IP that whois identifies as any part of government.
Of course  that doesn't mean anything. However, image boards were always glowing. We always found fed posters, so this being a target for surveillance is nothing new.
Opsec has always been quite the theme on image boards. Now it's even better in a way. With 8kun having a target painted on it's back, it's even less of a reason with being a lazy ass using opsec.

>>a5790d52-d941-4e7f-a545-20c68ccd7bef
I provide hosting as a side hustle. With the next upgrade cycle at the end of the year I'll dedicate 25mbit of uplink to seeding over TOR.
One of the question I always had is how do trackers play into the architecture of zeronet. Would it help if I setup a Zeronet tracker? If so, is there a resource someone can link on how to setup a zeronet tracker?
